# Architecture Compliance Remediation Plan

## Goal Description
To ensure the SENTINEL platform complies with 2026 U.S. Government architectural guidance (Zero Trust, Section 508), we will activate the latent security configurations and patch the UI for accessibility.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Zero Trust Activation:** Changes to [SecurityConfig.java](file:///d:/Projects/mercenary/src/main/java/com/jreinhal/mercenary/config/SecurityConfig.java) will enable strictly typed security for the `govcloud` profile. This will require valid X.509 certificates to access the application when running in that specific profile. The default `dev` profile will remain unaffected.

## Proposed Changes

### Security Layer (Zero Trust)
#### [MODIFY] [SecurityConfig.java](file:///d:/Projects/mercenary/src/main/java/com/jreinhal/mercenary/config/SecurityConfig.java)
- Uncomment the `govSecurityFilterChain` bean.
- Enable `http.x509()` authentication extraction.
- Ensure strict Principle of Least Privilege (PoLP) defaults.

### User Interface (Section 508)
#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///d:/Projects/mercenary/src/main/resources/static/index.html)
- Add `aria-label` attributes to all icon-only buttons (e.g., "Copy Response", "Expand", "Search").
- Add `role="img"` and `aria-hidden="true"` to decorative SVGs.
- Ensure status indicators have semantic text alternatives.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
1.  **Build Check:** Run `./gradlew clean build` to ensure the SecurityConfig changes compile correctly with the project dependencies.

### Manual Verification
1.  **Accessibility Audit:**
    - Open [index.html](file:///d:/Projects/mercenary/src/main/resources/static/index.html) (served via app).
    - Inspect Elements to verify `aria-label` presence on buttons.
2.  **Profile Safety Check:**
    - Start app in `dev` mode (`./gradlew bootRun`).
    - Verify app still loads and login works (Dev Mode bypass), confirming that the `govcloud` changes did not regress the development environment.
